 How to Create a User in Kibana (for Elasticsearch Security)
In Kibana, user management is handled by Elasticsearch's security features. You can create users via:
‚úÖ Kibana UI
‚úÖ Elasticsearch API

üîπ Prerequisite: You must have Elasticsearch Security enabled (Basic license includes authentication).

‚úÖ Method 1: Using Kibana UI (Easiest)
1Ô∏è‚É£ Login to Kibana as an admin.
2Ô∏è‚É£ Go to "Stack Management" ‚Üí "Security" ‚Üí "Users".
3Ô∏è‚É£ Click "Create user".
4Ô∏è‚É£ Fill in user details:

Username (e.g., new-user)
Password
Roles (e.g., kibana_user, read, or custom roles)
5Ô∏è‚É£ Click Save.
‚úÖ Now, the user can log in to Kibana with the assigned roles.



